headline: Visa (V) Shuts Down US Open-Banking Unit Amid Regulatory Uncertainty
summary: Visa Inc. (NYSE:V) is one of the best long-term stocks to invest in according to Warren Buffett. On August 22, the company shut down its US open-banking unit. A company spokesperson stated that Visa will now focus its open-banking strategy in high-potential markets like Europe and Latin America.
